I've been playing with [MediaPipe](https://github.com/google-ai-edge/mediapipe)'s hand tracking, its so fun. A lot of inspiration from the Generative Art community. For linkedin, the obvious use case was my own resume? so here it is:
- Try it: https://fsaudm.github.io/handcv/
- Repo/Code: https://github.com/fsaudm/HandCV

No mouse, no keyboard, just gestures. Tilt your left hand to scroll through sections. Open your right hand to expand, close it to collapse. It's weird and fun. 

Built it with vanilla JS + Canvas + MediaPipe, and a big dose of AI agents. Give it a try and let me know what you think! I have a few more ideas I want to try with this setup. In the mean time, Im out of here because I kinda hate linkedin 🙃.


